
[1]accusation

   ACCUSA'TION, n.

   1. The act of charging with a crime or offense; the act of accusing of
   any wrong or injustice.

   2. The charge of an offense or crime; or the declaration containing the
   charge.

   They set over his head his accusation. Mat. 27.
